```zsh
~$ jerrod --help

GitLab and GitHub merge request review tool - the reliable guardian of code quality

Usage: jerrod [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

Commands:
  start        Start a new merge request review session
  status       Show current review session status
  peek         View the next thread in the review queue
  pop          Remove a thread from the review queue
  resolve      Mark the current thread as resolved
  comment      Add a comment to a thread or MR
  commit       Commit changes with automatic MR/thread linking
  acknowledge  Acknowledge a comment with reaction
  finish       Finish the review session
  refresh      Refresh session data (clean and re-download)
  help         Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
      --github-token <GITHUB_TOKEN>  GitHub personal access token (or use GITHUB_TOKEN env var) [env: GITHUB_TOKEN=]
      --gitlab-token <GITLAB_TOKEN>  GitLab personal access token (or use GITLAB_TOKEN env var) [env: GITLAB_TOKEN=]
  -h, --help                         Print help
```

```zsh
~$ jerrod start --help

Start a new merge request review session

Usage: jerrod start [OPTIONS] <REPOSITORY> <MR_NUMBER>

Arguments:
  <REPOSITORY>  Repository URL or "owner/repo" format
  <MR_NUMBER>   Merge request/pull request number

Options:
  -p, --platform <PLATFORM>  Platform (github or gitlab) - auto-detected if not specified. Default: github
  -h, --help                 Print help
```

```zsh
~$ jerrod comment --help
Add a comment to a thread or MR

Usage: jerrod comment [OPTIONS] <TEXT>

Arguments:
  <TEXT>  Comment text

Options:
      --new   Create a new MR-level comment instead of replying to current thread
  -h, --help  Print help
```

```zsh
~$ jerrod commit --help
Commit changes with automatic MR/thread linking

Usage: jerrod commit [OPTIONS] <MESSAGE>

Arguments:
  <MESSAGE>  Commit message

Options:
  -d, --details <DETAILS>      Optional detailed description
  -t, --thread-id <THREAD_ID>  Thread ID being addressed (optional)
  -h, --help                   Print help
```
